The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | One dies in Kandhamal
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     One dies in Kandhamal
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Sept. 23: One person was killed as violence erupted in riot-hit Kandhamal district today after a brief lull.         
	Policemen opened fire to contain a 1,000-strong mob who attacked Raikia police station in the Orissa district. B. Pradhan, one of the protesters, died in the scuffle.         
	Two demonstrators and over 25 police personnel were injured.         
	Protesters, mostly women, were demanding lifting of curfew and prohibitory orders clamped after attacks on Christians, and immediate arrest of the killers of religious leader Laxmanand Saraswati.         
	Mulayam ban call        
	Samajwadi Party chief Mulayam Singh Yadav has demanded a ban on the Bajrang Dal for allegedly attacking missionaries in Orissa and Karnataka.                                                                                                                                                                          
